abstract: Mitch McConnell and the other 99 senators must serve the institution and the Constitution that established it, not President Trump.
snippet: Mitch McConnell and the other 99 senators must serve the institution and the Constitution that established it, not President Trump.
lead_paragraph: When the Senate ultimately convenes to consider whether to remove the president from office, for just the third time in its history, it will convene not as a legislative body, but as a court of impeachment. And it will not just be President Trump on trial. The Senate — and indeed, truth itself — will stand trial.

abstract: Indonesia will lower the threshold at which it begins to impose import taxes on consumer goods sold via e-commerce to just $3, from $75, to control purchases of cheap foreign products and protect small domestic firms, officials said on Monday.
snippet: Indonesia will lower the threshold at which it begins to impose import taxes on consumer goods sold via e-commerce to just $3, from $75, to control purchases of cheap foreign products and protect small domestic firms, officials said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: JAKARTA — Indonesia will lower the threshold at which it begins to impose import taxes on consumer goods sold via e-commerce to just $3, from $75, to control purchases of cheap foreign products and protect small domestic firms, officials said on Monday.
headline_main: Indonesia to Lower Threshold for Import Taxes on e-Commerce Goods
headline_print_headline: Indonesia to Lower Threshold for Import Taxes on e-Commerce Goods

abstract: China dismissed accusations of forced labor at a Shanghai prison on Monday, a day after media reports that a message had been found in a Christmas card saying it had been packed by inmates.
snippet: China dismissed accusations of forced labor at a Shanghai prison on Monday, a day after media reports that a message had been found in a Christmas card saying it had been packed by inmates.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING/LONDON — China dismissed accusations of forced labor at a Shanghai prison on Monday, a day after media reports that a message had been found in a Christmas card saying it had been packed by inmates.
headline_main: China Denies Forced Labor Accusations After Plea Found in Christmas Card
headline_print_headline: China Denies Forced Labor Accusations After Plea Found in Christmas Card

abstract: Nearly half of companies in South Africa had no taxable income in 2017 while a quarter recorded a taxable loss, the South African Revenue service said on Monday, based on its latest 2017/18 data, highlighting the impact of weak economic growth.
snippet: Nearly half of companies in South Africa had no taxable income in 2017 while a quarter recorded a taxable loss, the South African Revenue service said on Monday, based on its latest 2017/18 data, highlighting the impact of weak economic growth.
lead_paragraph: JOHANNESBURG — Nearly half of companies in South Africa had no taxable income in 2017 while a quarter recorded a taxable loss, the South African Revenue service said on Monday, based on its latest 2017/18 data, highlighting the impact of weak economic growth.
headline_main: Weak Economy Cuts Number of South African Companies Paying Tax
headline_print_headline: Weak Economy Cuts Number of South African Companies Paying Tax

abstract: Ferrari put their long-term faith in Charles Leclerc on Monday by extending the 22-year-old's contract for five more years until the end of 2024.
snippet: Ferrari put their long-term faith in Charles Leclerc on Monday by extending the 22-year-old's contract for five more years until the end of 2024.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Ferrari put their long-term faith in Charles Leclerc on Monday by extending the 22-year-old's contract for five more years until the end of 2024.

abstract: Libya’s forces based in the country’s east said Monday they have released a vessel with Turkish crew members seized over the weekend amid heightened tensions in the eastern Mediterranean over a contentious maritime border deal involving Tripoli and Ankara.

lead_paragraph: CAIRO — Libya’s forces based in the country’s east said Monday they have released a vessel with Turkish crew members seized over the weekend amid heightened tensions in the eastern Mediterranean over a contentious maritime border deal involving Tripoli and Ankara.
headline_main: Libya’s East-Based Forces Release Ship With Turkish Crew

abstract: AC Milan's dream of returning to the elite of European football looked more distant than ever after they gave what their own director described as an "embarrassing" performance in a 5-0 defeat to Atalanta on Sunday.

abstract: China will lower tariffs on products ranging from frozen pork and avocado to some types of semiconductors next year as Beijing looks to boost imports amid a slowing economy and a trade war with the United States.

abstract: The Russian government has vowed to retaliate against U.S. sanctions on a new Russia-Germany pipeline, work on which was suspended on Saturday.
